Only one vessel is required for the whole process, which should be of stone,
and should be capable of resisting fire. ... The vessel should be placed in a
reverberatory alembic. This should be set over a gentle fire, the vessel being
kept tightly closed, in order that it may be able to retain its companion,
and permit the same to enkindle the whiteness thereof, as Lucas says.
